”This is not the end; it is not even the beginning of the end
but perhaps, the end of the beginning 
For my mum - my best friend and role model
Anita Shaw 1948 2008"®
”In loving, everlasting memory of
Eden Harman Bernardy
"Love each other. Be kind to each other. Respect each other
And whenever you can, as much as you can,
LAUGH, DANCE, SING, & CELEBRATE LIFE"
Eden. your spirit lives within and around us. We love you
Beyond measure. Beyond words. ALWAYS"¬
¦CITY OF LONDON
In loving memory of
CAPTAIN DAVID SEATH
whose journey ended 3.2 miles short
and a lifetime too early.
Forever in our hearts. No one is left behind."¬
¦In fond memory of
Our Founder Mrs June Mackay
Our Chairman John Perry
and Secretary Mrs Louise Perry (nee Conner)
from the members of the Brixton Dog Training Club"▒
«To Baby Angelina
Our Beautiful angel, Our hearts are filled with sorrow for having left us so soon
We love you; Miss you every moment of everyday
Mum. Dad. Sister & Family"Ę
┤This seat is dedicated 
to the memory of
Arthur Barter
Welsh Guards

In memory of
Captain Robert (Bob) Clarkson
1936 - 2010
Scots Guards
A good friend of the guards museum"╣
